                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115C96/114</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Hostetter</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Hermosillo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-03-01T11:00:00-07:23">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 1, 1916, 11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s February 24, 6 p.m. Obregon just arrived and spoke to him about
                    Chihuahua district. Says he has sent additional troops with very good generals,
                    Herrera and Gutiérres, who thoroughly know country, with orders to push pursuit
                    and earnestly hopes to have district cleared very soon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hostetter</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
